class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bog1665702719152.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bog1665702719152.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bog1665702719152.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bog1665702719152\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Enable Uniface to handle foreign threads.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"bog1665702719152__topic_d139472e1_d139473e1_d139474e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bog1665702719152__p_d139475e1_d139476e1_d139477e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bog1665702719152__section_ndn_t5t_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1182288e68\"> Defaults </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bog1665702719152__table_d16646e1_d16647e1_d16648e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> client assignment files </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> [SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bog1665702719152__section_dfs_t5t_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1182288e114\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bog1665702719152__p_d139484e1_d139485e1_d139486e1\">The assignment setting\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS</span> allows Uniface to handle multiple threads by\n        serializing the invocation of COM objects.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"bog1665702719152__note_gtp_v5t_1wb\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Do not use\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS</span> unless you have also set <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Thread\n          Synchronization</span> using Uniface COM Configuration utility.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgr1665702879587.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring the COM Connector</a><p>The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xsz1665702892138.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Global Uniface COM Settings</a><p>Specify global options for the COM connector.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526156\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526156\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Enable Uniface to handle foreign threads. $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS = 1 | 0 Defaults Assignment file: client assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description The assignment setting $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS allows Uniface to handle multiple threads by serializing the invocation of COM objects. CAUTION: Do not use $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS unless you have also set Thread Synchronization using Uniface COM Configuration utility. Related Links Configuring the COM Connector The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications. Global Uniface COM Settings Specify global options for the COM connector. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}